Class AbstractCachingParser<T>

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
ILineParser<T>
public abstract class AbstractCachingParser<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ILineParser<T>

Objects that implement this interface are used to parse lines of data from data resource into data structures that are then manipulated by the dictionary.

setInitialCapacity

public void setInitialCapacity(int capacity)
Sets the initial capacity of the cache. This number controls how many objects can be added to the cache before it has to grow automatically. If the cache has already been initialized, this method has no effect until the cache is released (releaseCache()) and re-initialized (initializeCache(int)).

Parameters:
capacity - The initial capacity of the cache.

clear

public void clear()
Clears the cache.

initializeCache

protected void initializeCache(int capacity)
Initializes the cache. For internal setup. This method does not need to be called by subclasses, as it is automatically called by this class's constructor via the setCachingEnabled(boolean) method.

Parameters:
capacity - the initial capacity of the cache.

releaseCache

protected void releaseCache()
Releases the cache. For internal cleanup if required.

getCachedItem

protected T getCachedItem(java.lang.String line)
Returns the item cached for the specified line, if any.

Parameters:
line - the line for which an item is requested. If caching is disabled, this method returns null. This method is intended to be used by subclasses.
Returns:
The item, if found; if not found or caching is disabled, returns null

cacheItem

protected void cacheItem(java.lang.String line,
                         T item)
Caches the particular data structure for the indicated line. This means that this line was parsed to the specified item. If caching is disabled, this method does nothing. This method is intended to be used by subclasses.

Parameters:
line - the line that was parsed
item - the item that parsing the line produced
